Friedman died of heart failure at the age of 94 years in San Francisco on November 16, 2006.[63] He was still a working economist performing original economic research; his last column was published in The Wall Street Journal the day after his death.[64] He was survived by his wife (who would die on August 18, 2009) and their two children, David, known for the anarcho-capitalist book The Machinery of Freedom, and bridge expert Jan Martel.
